title: Grateful Dead Live at Ventura County Fairgrounds on 1983-07-31
description: Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, West L.A. Fadeaway, Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain-> Deal Hell In A Bucket-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E:Touch Of Gray-> E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Jerry's Brithday For a Jerry birthday show, there were very little highlights to celebrate.  Jerry looked out of it and was barely able to acknowledge the crowd as they sang happy birthday to him before Jack Straw.
Not as good as Saturday My 2nd show, and not nearly up to the level of the previous day. You can skip this one. Although the Saturday Night encore on Sunday was kind of fun!

Different Take..... This audience tape starts a little warbly but gets its sea-legs by West L.A. I know this show is like the ugly step-child to the night before but it really deserves a better fate.  The second set is hypnotic and filled with vivid imagery and echolalic verbosity.  Pretty hot pre-drums Scarlet>Fire and than Jerry takes a break to chase the dragon.  Space>Other One is lucid and full of intricate ensemble jamming.  18 minutes later Wharf appears from the mist with Garcia getting full use from his torn vocal chords.  Like the China Doll from 7/30 he pours his heart into each lyric enciting the crowd into erotic pleasure.  The jam that ensues is a Mydland-fest coupled with a nice helping of the tiger axe. Garcia's hands were caked with residue throughout the show and he probably hadn't showered in days but this is pure '83 magic and is a hidden gem amongst many more recognized recordings.

a nice trip I don't think this as poor as some think. No, the recording isn't great, but I've heard way worse. I have only heard the second set so far so take that into account. I really like 79-84 a lot, so maybe I have some bias there, but I've found this to be a pleasant listening experience. Definitely better shows, for playing and SQ out there, but without the sbds available anymore, we must embrace the audience recordings, and I love it. The FEEL!!
It rips! The show and recording rips! I don't know what the naysayers are smoking or not smoking but this is a great AUD.

Rippin set! Great audience show. I was quite pleasantly suprised about this show and how good it sounded from the audince quality perspective. It takes about 2 minutes to get used to the audience quality ( I have 95% sbds) so this was an aquired taste- I am very happy to have given it a shot. 

The intro on bucket is slinky and sort of 'confised' as it is still beign refined as a new tune. The scarlet is very tight- great long inro- they jam for 1:31 before garcia hits the firts verse.  Nice long fun intro. Crowd is into it but you do no hear but a few people. There is no crowd noice to this audience show. I had this blasitng last night on my way back from a family outing and it was on fire. Check out the other >warfrat. Jerry sings sooo sweetly- his inflexctions adn holding of the notes lets us know he is not just singing this for the heck of it- he is into it. NFA to close was tetering on 70's style jamming. 

I give this show a 3.5 starts for sound and a 5 stars for what I hear iin the music, unlike rob001 below who has decided he needs to type in all caps adn be angry about wind and heat...dude get oover it. The show rocks. I wish there was a sbd of it. Scarlet>fire is 25 minutes long. It may have been hot but the miusic never sufffered. 
I was not there and saw my first show 4 years after this one. A ocnservative 4 stars for thi sh0w. You will nto be disappointed unless all you every listended to you entire life is A+ sbds. 

This show deserves respect in the lineage of deadshows.
uh huh I was at this one too. The Scarlet-fire is on of my faves. :)

7-31-83 Man ,I had this tape back in the 80's when I was a teenager, and I was just glad to have this show with a great Scarlet>Fire.Brent's playing was so tight back then.Friends of mine who went weren't all that impressed,but they played this tape all the time.What sounds good at the show ,and what sounds good on tape doesn't always match up.I went to some great shows ,and it seems no matter which recordings I hear they never quite capture what I witnessed,whereas some shows I thought were lame came out good on tape.Goes to show ,you don't ever know !

better than you think Went to all Ventura shows and listening to this one is pretty good overall. Whoever gave it a 1 is just not listening. It sounds pretty nice to me. I remember seeing Jerry sitting in a chair behind the stage shaking his head like he was really stoned, trying to shake it off. And a double encore to boot. Not a very common occurance in Dead shows. They must have been on.
JACK STRAW While the aud recording may not be amazing, check out the sbd and listen to phils bass on the jack straw, this show is severly underrated and this jack straw proves it.

Happy Birthday I was at this show and all the Ventura shows from '82-'85.

I want to add to the first post who complained about Garcia not acknowledging the crowd for a pre-show 'Happy Birthday'.  I honestly don't even remember a pre-show rendition. Must not have been much. 
But what I do recall is that at the end of Not Fade Away, after the crowd chant quieted, the band came out for the encore.  Bob, Phil and Jerry took their positions at the mics, Drummers and Brent their seats.  Then suddenly they all, except Jerry, hurried to just off-stage leaving Jerry alone at his mic in front of the crowd.  That's when 'Happy Birthday' was sung. An embarrassed Jerry looked over at his laughing bandmates and painfully endured our affection.
No, he didn't say anything to the crowd. But we did get a double encore.

An exceptional Deal, the rest is solid summer '83 stuff.

my recollections Phil is hot , love the bass jams on jack straw through Mexicali , nice version of me and my uncle into Mexicali , groovin dancing shakin was going on ....  jerry may have been wasted but a wasted Jerry better than most in the world
